/*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*\
  evaporator04_orange_juice_simple  --  MCFT Ex. 10.2 (a)-(c).

  Single-effect evaporator concentrating orange juice.

  Problem (textbook givens):
    Feed          25 000 kg/h orange juice, 20 °C (293 K), 10 wt% solids
    Target        productConc = 50 wt% solids
    P_process     14 kPa  (vacuum; keeps T_boil low for thermolabile juice)
    Heating       saturated steam at 2 bar (200 kPa)
    U             2840 W/(m²·K)
    Cp_solution   4.18 kJ/(kg·K) (built into `solidos` Cp_mol = 752.4 J/(mol·K))
    BPE           negligible for parts (a)-(c).  Part (d) uses the
                  Capriste-Lozano correlation --- skipped here; a separate
                  tutorial picks it up later.

  Wiring (the simplest credo case):

      feed (25000 kg/h, 10 % at 293 K)              productConc (5000 kg/h, 50 %)
            |                                                    ^
            v                                                    |
      +-----------------------------------------------+
      |              evaporator (single effect)        |
      |   P = 14 kPa  area = $A  U = 2840 W/m²/K       |
      +-----+-----+----+----+----+----+----+----+-----+
            ^                            |          |
            |                            v          v
       liveSteam (200 kPa)            vapour       condensate
       (vapor de aquecimento)         (20000 kg/h) (= F_steam)
                                       -> condenser

  What the textbook asks:
    a)  Heat-transfer area               --> KPI  effect1.A_needed
    b)  Heating-steam flow               --> KPI  effect1.F_steam_kg_h
    c)  Capacity (V evaporated) + economy --> KPI  effect1.F_vap, .economy

  How the case answers in Choupo
  -------------------------------
  The DesignSpec in `system/outerDict` manipulates $F_steam (the only
  free variable here, with $A merely "for sizing") until the product
  outlet hits 5000 kg/h.  Then the evaporator reports A_needed, the
  economy, all duties.

  Expected results after convergence (textbook ballpark):
    productConc        :  5000 kg/h @ 50 wt% solids  (exact)
    Capacity V_evap    :  20000 kg/h water           (mass balance)
    Q_duty             :  ~ 14.1 MW
    F_steam            :  ~ 23 000 kg/h saturated steam at 2 bar
    A_needed           :  ~ 73 m²
    Economy            :  ~ 0.87  (single-effect; cold feed eats sensible)
\*---------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

variables
{
    // DUAS INCÓGNITAS do problema textbook (Ex. 10.2 a, b):
    //   $A        : área de transferência (a resposta à pergunta a)
    //   $F_steam  : caudal de vapor de aquecimento (resposta à pergunta b)
    // Ambas iteradas pelo DesignSpec.  Os valores aqui são apenas
    // chutes iniciais para o Newton-ND 2-D arrancar.
    A          80.0   m2;
    F_steam   500.0   kmol/h;
}

streams
{
    feed
    {
        T             293.15 K;          // 20 °C
        P             100.0  kPa;        // atmosférica (tag only)
        massFlows                         // total 25000 kg/h, 10 wt% solidos
        {
            agua      22500.0  kg/h;
            solidos    2500.0  kg/h;
        }
    }

    liveSteam_200kPa
    {
        F                $F_steam;
        P                200.0  kPa;
        state            saturatedVapour;   // -> T = T_sat(200 kPa) ~ 393 K
        molarComposition  { agua 1.0; }
        category         LP_steam_200kPa;   // utility tag for aggregation
    }
}

units
(
    {
        name        evap;
        type        evaporator;
        inputs      ( feed  liveSteam_200kPa );
        outputs     ( productConc  vapour  condensate );
        operation
        {
            // HARDWARE (Mode 2, credo-pure):
            //   - area: heat-exchange surface  (iterated by DesignSpec to
            //                                   hit P_op = 14 kPa textbook spec)
            //   - U:    overall HTC            (textbook datum, constant)
            // P_op of the vessel EMERGES from the heat balance + saturation
            // curve; appears as KPI evap.P.  The DesignSpec constrains it.
            area        $A;
            U         2840.0   W/m2/K;
        }
    }
);
